standard_metadata.standard_description: Use ratio and rate reasoning to solve real-world and mathematical problems, e.g., by reasoning about tables of equivalent ratios, tape diagrams, double number line diagrams, or equations.

question.content: The square below represents one whole.      **What percent is represented by the shaded area?**   $\%$

images.alt: An array with 10 columns and 10 rows that represents 1 whole.  4 rows of 10 are shaded. 1 row of 3 is shaded.

hints.content: Percent means per-hundred.  Each big square is split into $100$ equal pieces, or *hundredths*.   So, each of the $100$ small squares represent $1\%$.
$\blueD{43 \text{ hundredths}}$ are shaded.
$\blueD{43 \text{ hundredths}}= \blueD{43}$ per hundred $=\blueD{43}\%$
$\blueD{43}\%$ is represented by the shaded area.
